15.title: MeTube

16.body: MeTube is a web interface for youtube-dl . It's a simple downloader for YouTube videos and playlists.

17.body: Paste your URL on the homepage, choose your format/quality and click on the download button. The download will start automatically. At the end of the download, you will be redirected to the download page. You can download the file. Please ensure you delete the downloaded files after you get them. The /forge team isn't not responsible for the content you download.

21.body: The idea behind the cloud part of the /forge is to provide a self-hosted alternative to the Google Suite. We can now ensure that our data is not used by Google to make money.
21.title: Concept

22.body: NextCloud Alternative to Google Drive, Dropbox, etc. OnlyOffice Alternative to Google Docs, Microsoft Office, etc. PhotoPrism Alternative to Google Photos, Apple Photos, etc.

4.title: #3 Deploy infrastructure (using Terraform)

5.body: Local Configuration To deploy the /forge infrastructure, you will need: Ansible Terraform This two tools must be installed on your local machine. The installation process installs the following tools on the remote machine: Docker Docker Compose Git zsh Host Configuration The configuration is tested only for Debian, I can't guarantee that it will work on other distributions. There are few requirements for the remote hosts: All the hosts must have the same user with root privileges. All the IPs address must be written in the ansible/hosts.yml file.
5.title: Requirements
